Statistical Tests

## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  yfdn$stars and yfdn$review_count
## t = -119.34, df = 192159, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -30.51586 -29.52972
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##  3.589347 33.612137

#null Hypothesis : Review count for each ratings are equally distributed. #AS p value is low , we will reject null hypothesis. #this means review count across each star rating are different

##  [1] "coefficients"  "residuals"     "effects"       "rank"

## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

#Null hypothesis : review_count are equally distributed across categories #P value is low so we will reject null hypothesis. #which means review counts are not equally distributed across categories
